  "an9.28:3.3": "So that fear and enmity is quelled for anyone who refrains from consuming beer, wine, and liquor intoxicants. ",
  "an9.28:3.4": "These are the five fears and enmities they have quelled. ",
  "an9.28:4.1": "What are the four factors of stream-entry that they possess? ",
  "an9.28:4.2": "When a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha … ",
  "an9.28:4.3": "",
  "an9.28:4.4": "the teaching … ",
  "an9.28:4.5": "the Saṅgha … ",
  "an9.28:4.6": "And a noble disciple’s ethical conduct is loved by the noble ones, unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred, liberating, praised by sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion. ",
  "an9.28:4.7": "These are the four factors of stream-entry that they possess. ",
  "an9.28:5.1": "When a noble disciple has quelled these five fears and enmities, and possesses these four factors of stream-entry, they may, if they wish, declare of themselves: ",
  "an9.28:5.2": "‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am destined for awakening.’” ",
  "an9.29:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 9.29 ",
  "an9.29:0.2": "3. Abodes of Sentient Beings ",
  "an9.29:0.3": "Grounds for Resentment ",
  "an9.29:1.1": "“Mendicants, there are nine grounds for resentment. ",
  "an9.29:1.2": "What nine? ",
  "an9.29:1.3": "Thinking: ‘They did wrong to me,’ you harbor resentment. ",
  "an9.29:1.4": "Thinking: ‘They are doing wrong to me’ … ",
  "an9.29:1.5": "‘They will do wrong to me’ … ",
  "an9.29:1.6": "‘They did wrong to someone I love’ … ",
  "an9.29:1.7": "‘They are doing wrong to someone I love’ … ",
  "an9.29:1.8": "‘They will do wrong to someone I love’ … ",
  "an9.29:1.9": "‘They helped someone I dislike’ … ",
  "an9.29:1.10": "‘They are helping someone I dislike’ … ",
  "an9.29:1.11": "Thinking: ‘They will help someone I dislike,’ you harbor resentment. ",
  "an9.29:1.12": "These are the nine grounds for resentment.” ",
  "an9.30:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 9.30 ",
  "an9.30:0.2": "3. Abodes of Sentient Beings ",
  "an9.30:0.3": "Getting Rid of Resentment ",
  "an9.30:1.1": "“Mendicants, there are these nine ways to get rid of resentment. ",
  "an9.30:1.2": "What nine? ",
  "an9.30:1.3": "Thinking: ‘They harmed me, but what can I possibly do?’ you get rid of resentment. ",
  "an9.30:1.4": "Thinking: ‘They are harming me …’ … ",
  "an9.30:1.5": "‘They will harm me …’ … ",
  "an9.30:1.6": "‘They harmed someone I love …’ … ",
  "an9.30:1.7": "‘They are harming someone I love …’ ",
  "an9.30:1.8": "‘They will harm someone I love …’ … ",
  "an9.30:1.9": "‘They helped someone I dislike …’ … ",
  "an9.30:1.10": "‘They are helping someone I dislike …’ … ",
  "an9.30:1.11": "Thinking: ‘They will help someone I dislike, but what can I possibly do?’ you get rid of resentment. ",
  "an9.30:1.12": "These are the nine ways to get rid of resentment.” ",
  "an9.31:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 9.31 ",
  "an9.31:0.2": "3. Abodes of Sentient Beings ",
  "an9.31:0.3": "Progressive Cessations ",
  "an9.31:1.1": "“Mendicants, there are these nine progressive cessations. ",
  "an9.31:1.2": "What nine? ",
  "an9.31:1.3": "For someone who has attained the first absorption, sensual perceptions have ceased. ",
  "an9.31:1.4": "For someone who has attained the second absorption, the placing of the mind and keeping it connected have ceased. ",
  "an9.31:1.5": "For someone who has attained the third absorption, rapture has ceased. ",
  "an9.31:1.6": "For someone who has attained the fourth absorption, breathing has ceased. ",
  "an9.31:1.7": "For someone who has attained the dimension of infinite space, the perception of form has ceased. ",
  "an9.31:1.8": "For someone who has attained the dimension of infinite consciousness, the perception of the dimension of infinite space has ceased. ",
  "an9.31:1.9": "For someone who has attained the dimension of nothingness, the perception of the dimension of infinite consciousness has ceased. ",
  "an9.31:1.10": "For someone who has attained the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, the perception of the dimension of nothingness has ceased. ",
  "an9.31:1.11": "For someone who has attained the cessation of perception and feeling, perception and feeling have ceased. ",
  "an9.31:1.12": "These are the nine progressive cessations.” ",
