  "an9.50:0.3": "Extinguishment in a Certain Respect ",
  "an9.50:1.1": "“Reverend, they speak of ‘extinguishment in a certain respect’. …” ",
  "an9.51:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 9.51 ",
  "an9.51:0.2": "5. Similarity ",
  "an9.51:0.3": "Extinguishment in This Life ",
  "an9.51:1.1": "“Reverend, they speak of ‘extinguishment in this life’. ",
  "an9.51:1.2": "In what way did the Buddha speak of extinguishment in this life?” ",
  "an9.51:2.1": "“First, take a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures … enters and remains in the first absorption. ",
  "an9.51:2.2": "To this extent the Buddha spoke of extinguishment in this life in a qualified sense. … ",
  "an9.51:3.1": "Furthermore, take a mendicant who, going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, enters and remains in the cessation of perception and feeling. And, having seen with wisdom, their defilements come to an end. ",
  "an9.51:3.2": "To this extent the Buddha spoke of extinguishment in this life in a definitive sense.” ",
