  "an9.55:1.1": "“Reverend, they speak of ‘reaching freedom from death’. …” ",
  "an9.56:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 9.56 ",
  "an9.56:0.2": "6. A Safe Place ",
  "an9.56:0.3": "A Place Without Fear ",
  "an9.56:1.1": "“Reverend, they speak of ‘a place without fear’. …” ",
  "an9.57:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 9.57 ",
  "an9.57:0.2": "6. A Safe Place ",
  "an9.57:0.3": "Reaching a Place Without Fear ",
  "an9.57:1.1": "“Reverend, they speak of ‘reaching a place without fear’. …” ",
  "an9.58:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 9.58 ",
  "an9.58:0.2": "6. A Safe Place ",
  "an9.58:0.3": "Tranquility ",
  "an9.58:1.1": "“Reverend, they speak of ‘tranquility’. …” ",
  "an9.59:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 9.59 ",
  "an9.59:0.2": "6. A Safe Place ",
  "an9.59:0.3": "Progressive Tranquility ",
  "an9.59:1.1": "“Reverend, they speak of ‘progressive tranquility’. …” ",
  "an9.60:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 9.60 ",
  "an9.60:0.2": "6. A Safe Place ",
  "an9.60:0.3": "Cessation ",
  "an9.60:1.1": "“Reverend, they speak of ‘cessation’. …” ",
  "an9.61:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 9.61 ",
  "an9.61:0.2": "6. A Safe Place ",
  "an9.61:0.3": "Progressive Cessation ",
  "an9.61:1.1": "“Reverend, they speak of ‘progressive cessation’. ",
  "an9.61:1.2": "What is the progressive cessation that the Buddha spoke of?” ",
  "an9.61:2.1": "“First, take a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures … enters and remains in the first absorption. ",
  "an9.61:2.2": "To this extent the Buddha spoke of progressive cessation in a qualified sense. … ",
  "an9.61:3.1": "Furthermore, take a mendicant who, going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, enters and remains in the cessation of perception and feeling. And, having seen with wisdom, their defilements come to an end. ",
  "an9.61:3.2": "To this extent the Buddha spoke of progressive cessation in a definitive sense.” ",
  "an9.62:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 9.62 ",
  "an9.62:0.2": "6. A Safe Place ",
  "an9.62:0.3": "Impossible ",
  "an9.62:1.1": "“Mendicants, without giving up nine things you can’t realize perfection. ",
  "an9.62:1.2": "What nine? ",
  "an9.62:1.3": "Greed, hate, delusion, anger, acrimony, disdain, contempt, jealousy, and stinginess. ",
  "an9.62:1.4": "Without giving up these nine things you can’t realize perfection. ",
  "an9.62:2.1": "After giving up nine things you can realize perfection. ",
  "an9.62:2.2": "What nine? ",
  "an9.62:2.3": "Greed, hate, delusion, anger, acrimony, disdain, contempt, jealousy, and stinginess. ",
  "an9.62:2.4": "After giving up these nine things you can realize the fruit of perfection.” ",
